12 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
13 INDICATED.
14 (2) “EQUIPMENT DEFECT” MEANS:
15 (I) A HOT WHEEL;
16 (II) A HOT WHEEL BEARING;
17 (III) A DEFECTIVE WHEEL BEARING DETECTED THROUGH
18 ACOUSTICS;
19 (IV) DRAGGING EQUIPMENT;
20 (V) EXCESSIVE TRAIN CAR HEIGHT OR WEIGHT;
21 (VI) A SHIFTED LOAD;
22 (VII) A LOW AIR HOSE;
23 (VIII) A RAIL TEMPERATURE DEFECT; OR
24 (IX) A WHEEL CONDITION DEFECT.
25 (3) “WAYSIDE DETECTOR SYSTEM” MEANS AN ELECTRONIC DEVICE
26 OR A SERIES OF CONNECTED OR NETWORKED DEVICES THAT SCAN PASSING TRAINS,

4 SENATE BILL 855
1 ROLLING STOCK, AND ON–TRACK EQUIPMENT FOR DEFECTS.
2 (B) THIS SECTION APPLIES ONLY TO A RAILROAD COMPANY THAT OWNS OR
3 IS OTHERWISE RESPONSIBLE FOR A RAILROAD TRACK THAT THE FEDERAL
4 RAILROAD ADMINISTRATION HAS DESIGNATED CLASS IV OR GREATER.
5 (C) (1) EACH RAILROAD COMPANY SHALL INSTALL A WAYSIDE DETECTOR
6 SYSTEM ON RAILROAD TRACKS OWNED OR OTHERWISE UNDER THE RESPONSIBILITY
7 OF THE RAILROAD COMPANY THAT THE FEDERAL RAILROAD ADMINISTRATION HAS
8 DESIGNATED CLASS IV OR GREATER.
9 (2) (I) EACH RAILROAD COMPANY SHALL INSTALL, MAINTAIN,
10 REPAIR, AND OPERATE EACH WAYSIDE DETECTOR SYSTEM IN ACCORDANCE WITH
11 ALL APPLICABLE GUIDELINES AND REGULATIONS ADOPTED BY THE FEDERAL
12 DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION.
13 (II) A RAILROAD COMPANY SHALL REMOVE AND REPLACE AN
14 EXPIRED, BROKEN, OR OBSOLETE WAYSIDE DETECTOR SYSTEM OR PART OF A
15 WAYSIDE DETECTOR SYSTEM.
16 (III) A RAILROAD COMPANY SHALL PLACE EACH WAYSIDE
17 DETECTOR SYSTEM AT AN APPROPRIATE DISTANCE, AS DETERMINED BY THE
18 COMMISSIONER, FROM OTHER WAYSIDE DETECTOR SYSTEMS AND AT A LOCATION
19 THAT WILL ALLOW A TRAIN OPERATOR SUFFICIENT TIME TO:
20 1. RESPOND TO AN ALERT RECEIVED FROM THE
21 WAYSIDE DETECTOR SYSTEM;
22 2. IF NECESSARY, STOP THE TRAIN, ROLLING STOCK, OR
23 ON–TRACK EQUIPMENT; AND
24 3. IF NECESSARY, MAKE REPAIRS OR REMOVE
25 EQUIPMENT THAT IS FOUND BY THE TRAIN OPERATOR TO BE DEFECTIVE.
26 (3) (I) EACH RAILROAD COMPANY SHALL ESTABLISH WRITTEN
27 POLICIES AND TRAINING REQUIREMENTS FOR THE RAILROAD COMPANY’S
28 EMPLOYEES FOR:
29 1. MONITORING FOR ALERTS FROM WAYSIDE DETECTOR
30 SYSTEMS; AND
31 2. RESPONDING TO ALERTS RECEIVED FROM WAYSIDE
32 DETECTOR SYSTEMS.

